{
  "texts": [
    "Despite considerable effort, the return on investment was minimal, with only one or two relevant papers found that included AI practitioners' views on ethics in AI for every hundred papers.",
    "This experience taught us that for a very new research topic with highly specific inclusion and exclusion criteria, it is not worth going through the titles and abstracts of all the papers in the initial search due to the expected low return on investment.",
    "From our initial search, we found only 13 papers.",
    "Since, Wolfswinkel et al. (2013) welcome adaptations to their framework by acknowledging that \"... one size does not fit all, and there should be no hesitation whatsoever to deviate from our proposed steps, as long as such variation is well motivated\", we conducted forward and backward snowballing on those 13 articles.",
    "During the snowballing process, we had to modify our seed review protocol to find relevant papers that had information on AI practitioners' views on ethics in AI."
  ]
}